(8,	11,	'',	'network outage',	'There were several server down incidents received. After short investigation is there for now one sign – all do have the same subnet IP: 213.1.150.*\r\n\r\nI called CIM and he initialized ticket creation for T-SYSTEMS to check it.\r\n\r\nPlease provide me the ticket id and ask for regular updates.\r\n\r\nHello L1 team,\r\n… following esl have the ip next nodes :\r\nduss0338.gsa.westlb.net\r\nduss0626.gsa.westlb.net\r\nduss1121.gsa.westlb.net \r\nduss1122.gsa.westlb.net\r\nduss1331.gsa.westlb.net\r\nduss1332.gsa.westlb.net\r\n\r\nare there some other nodes down incidents ?\r\n',	'2014:02:28'),
(9,	11,	'',	'navrh',	'poslal som Birgit tento navrh:\r\n\r\nHello Birgit\r\n\r\nI realize you’re busy with more important stuff but I have got small proposal for you how to improve process and communication between HP and Portigon…We have discovered that there missing some processes in case Portigon request something in case what have in my mind and it’s about decommissioning of the database. From our point of view it’s clear and we know what to do. But from communication between application team at Portigon and us I have realized they don’t know what to do and such clearly defined process probably does not exists or not all of them are informed about. As the result they mix two different requests into one and they send separate requests to other teams thought it should be part of one request or one process.\r\n\r\nI apologize with disturbing about but in my opinion it needs to be clarified.\r\n',	'2014:03:06'),
(10,	11,	'',	'Odpoved Birgit',	'Hi Thomas ! Hi Vlastimil !\r\n\r\nFirst of all I would like to thank you Thomas for your ideas of improvements. I am fully with you. There are lots of process issues on customer side which causes additional work on our side. \r\n\r\nSomehow I agree to Vlastimil but nevertheless I appreciate any suggestions, etc. \r\nAs Vlastimil mentions we are in the phase of negotiations of a new contract and in addition it looks like there will be lots of changes on customer side with regards to employees. I have heard that some people we are currently working with will leave the company. \r\nFurthermore I got promised by Manfred that I will have a contact person in the future I can directly work with. I hope this will be implemented as the current mode how we are acting is not really to my convenience. \r\n\r\nAs soon as such roles are implemented I would like to talk about such details you are mentioning here and bring them up.\r\n\r\nSorry for not responding earlier !\r\n',	'2014:03:12'),
(11,	11,	'',	'Vlastova odpoved',	'Thomas I am not optimistic in setting any processes to be followed by customer when they were not followed so far, \r\nand there are strategically changes on customer side with objective to get signed new contract.\r\n\r\nIf you have any proposal for improvements, then I would focus on our HP side ( Datacenter, Front End, Banking Demands area ), especially Banking demands  \r\n\r\n\r\nAppreciate your initiative \r\n',	'2014:03:12'),
(12,	9,	'',	'SQL issue on the server husbtsdb10.hus.fi',	'Hello,\r\n   Please open problem ticket for SQL team on the server husbtsdb10.hus.fi because we have issues on last night:\r\nEvent id:208\r\nSQL Server Scheduled Job \'DTA Purge and Archive (BizTalkDTADb)\' (0xFBC394E3384B2A40B65FA0261996BF1C) - Status: Failed - Invoked on: 2014-03-14 05:36:00 - Message: The job failed.  Unable to determine if the owner (HUS\\fujitsuadmin) of job DTA Purge and Archive (BizTalkDTADb) has server access (reason: Unable to connect to server - check SQL Server and SQL Server Agent errorlogs).\r\nEvent id:208\r\nSQL Server Scheduled Job \'DTA Purge and Archive (BizTalkDTADb)\' (0xFBC394E3384B2A40B65FA0261996BF1C) - Status: Failed - Invoked on: 2014-03-14 05:40:16 - Message: The job failed.  Unable to determine if the owner (HUS\\fujitsuadmin) of job DTA Purge and Archive (BizTalkDTADb) has server access (reason: Unable to connect to server - check SQL Server and SQL Server Agent errorlogs).\r\nWe need high priority problem management for this issue. Use P1 priority.\r\nThanks.\r\n',	'2014:03:14'),
(13,	5,	'',	'DR - 14.3.2014',	'During recovery test we have discovered one thing - the database PwManager that should be located on gbswipsqldb01.global.rexam.net in reality doeas not exists.',	'2014:03:14'),
(14,	9,	'',	'problem s biztalk2010 clustrom',	'Cau Tomas,\r\n\r\nMame problem s biztalk2010 clustrom a okrem ineho co mse nasli, sa casto opakuje aplikacny event ID 4104, ked som o tom nieco hladal, narazil som okrem ineho na toto:\r\n\r\n\r\nJust had this problem with our system test environment. The environment has been working for12+ months (with MSDTC configured for distributed transactions), then starting getting the MSDTC on server \'server\' is unavailable error a couple of days ago. DTCPing showed that MSDTC was working OK. SQL Server appeared to be working OK also. Tried the fix above, but that didn\'t work. Was just about to rebuild the DB server when I noticed a log file for one of the databases was exceptionally large (5.7Gb, DB is only 100Mb). Truncated the log file and everything started working again. Best guess is the log file was corrupted and this was somehow preventing SQL Server from rolling back and/or checking for aborteddistributed transaction. There were no SQL Server Log or Event Log entries that I could find to indicate a problem with the database or the DB log file. Note that the database with the corrupt log file was not the oneused by our application. Also,that DB did not need to participate in any distributed transactions.\r\n\r\nTak som nasiel tiez nejaky vacsi log “BizTalkMsgBoxDb_log” mozes sa  na to pozriet plz, neviem o SQLku nic\r\n',	'2014-03-17'),
