(30,	11,	'',	'LONS386',	'Hello Birgit, Vlastimil\r\n\r\nThis is to inform you we have been experiencing with following incident:\r\n\r\n•	There was issue at the lons386.emea.westlb server where the customer has been experiencing not working backups on the server from database point of view and the transaction has been growing very extremely in few days (400 GB). Normal size of this is around 70 GBs.  After investigation we’ve discovered the backups and other maintenance jobs were running on account that was disabled thus all jobs stopped working and transaction log has cleaned up\r\n•	During investigation we have also found out that we have just limited access to this server meaning that read only permissions due to person who has installed the server assumed from unknown reason our group has sufficient right but he was probably wrong \r\n•	We have contacted a lot of people from platform team including Euwan Walsh, Stephen Clarke, Phil Robertson to gain full admin access but a lot of  attempts to resolve  access issue by changing of security setting of the accounts we use for our support but didn’t help us\r\n•	We tried to get the credential for service accounts from the london’s platform team but nobody was able to provide us this. I also made walk-through all documentation I have but without any success. We have also contacted Chris Helm to get more information but he hasn’t have sufficient information.\r\n•	As the workaround we have proposed to restart SQL server into single user mode, setup own account of course with sufficient rights and restart the server back into multi user mode with expected downtime 20 minutes max.\r\n•	Customer has not agreed for first time with this workaround but after we have exhausted all options the customer has agreed with our workaround and approved downtime during Portigon’s out of office hours meaning that 16:30 UK time.\r\n•	Originally planned 20 minutes outage we’ve shortened to 10 minutes including with testing and customer’s conformation the server is running for them.\r\n•	Necessary changes have been made by Lukas Fras from GOC team. \r\n•	During this incident we also found that database monitoring is not working properly so we will fix it during upcoming days\r\n•	The customer also asked us to investigate why the transaction log has been growing so extremely.\r\n\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\n',	'2014-04-16'),
(31,	11,	'',	'Vlastova poznamka',	'Ahoj\r\n\r\n                                Vdaka za tu dobru pracu pre UK, feedback som zdielal aj s accountom a aj s Milom.\r\n\r\n                                Nakolko pracujes pre GSA a UK, mal by si pouzivat extra WBS pre kazdy region - > Je tak ? \r\n\r\n                                Co sa tyka trackovania ma trapi jedna vec, \r\n\r\n-	V accounte plati interne pravidlo, ze ludia mozu trackovat max 140 hodin mesacne, ak demand presahuje toto cislo treba informovat ADM-a ze toto cislo bude presiahnute a preco\r\n-	Dalej mame interne HP zalezitosti, ako su coffee talks, treningy, meetingy ( napr s Milom ) , citanie HP internych emailov a pod.toto sa nemoze trackovat na account\r\n-	Na zaver si spominal ze pracujes aj na externych veciach pre inych zakaznikov ako je Portigon, tento cas sa tiez nemoze trackovat na Portigon\r\n\r\nChcel by som ta teda poziadat o dodrziavanie tohto pravidla, je celkom jednoduche Ne-Portigon zalezitosti na Account nejdu, Portigon zalezitosti ano pricom sa delia na UK a GSA, a ini zakaznici na Portigon nejdu. \r\n\r\nAk je demand vacsi ako planovanych 140 hodin na mesiac, v tom pripade treba o tom informovat ADM-a ( mna ) \r\n',	'2014-04-22'),
