(42,	5,	'',	'CAB/TAB',	'Hi All,\r\n\r\nFollowing discussions with Theodora, we would like to set up a weekly HP internal TAB/CAB meeting. Our preference is for this internal meeting to take place prior to the Rexam weekly TAB & CAB meetings. It is recommended that each area is represented on the HP TAB/CAB meeting. Not only will this give everyone visibility of all the HP changes that are scheduled over the next couple of weeks, but will also give people the opportunity to raise any questions regarding the RFC’s. I would also like to cover off any changes that were scheduled from the previous 7 days, points on the meeting below:\r\n\r\n•	The meeting will be scheduled for 10:30 (UK time) every Tuesday. Initially the meeting will be scheduled for 30 minutes, but this may need to be increased if necessary. The current weekly AST meeting scheduled between 10:00 – 11:00 on Tuesday will be reduced to 30 minutes to accommodate the HP change meeting.\r\n•	Reports will be issued each Monday showing list of changes scheduled for implementation over the next two weeks. A second report will also be issued showing changes that had been scheduled for implementation from the previous week with their current status. Teams will need to review the reports prior to the meeting so the below points can be covered in the meeting:\r\n\r\n•	Review changes scheduled to be implemented in the next 2 weeks (this may need to be reviewed, if the number of changes is too large). \r\no	Are the approvals in place to implement the change?\r\no	Any concerns or queries with the change?\r\no	Will implementation of an RFC clash with any other change or activity?\r\n•	Review RFC’s from the previous 7 days for the below points:\r\no	RFC’s that have been implemented, has the PIR section of RFC form updated and Change Management notified?  \r\no	Any RFC’s that did not get implemented and why?\r\no	Any issues when implementing an RFC?\r\n\r\nThe first meeting will be scheduled for next Tuesday 10th June, a meeting invite will be sent out to all of you. \r\n\r\nThis is the first meeting, so the format of the meeting may change, if you have any suggestions please raise them.\r\n',	'2014-07-07'),
(43,	5,	'',	'FSC of outages / maintenance activities for Swindon DC',	'Hi All,\r\n\r\nI have a meeting with Rexam early tomorrow morning to discuss forward schedule of change in Swindon. This meeting will cover all the required activities that require outages that will impact Rexam for the next 6 – 12 months.  Below is a list of the activities I am aware of, can you please review and advise of anything that need to be included.  I may need to have a quick chat with some of you to discuss some of these points.\r\n\r\n•	Procurve switch activities – adding resilience.\r\n•	Blade enclosure firmware upgrades. 6 enclosure that contain Unix and Windows servers.\r\n•	Failover testing of Windows servers\r\n•	Failover testing of Unix servers\r\n•	Service Guard upgrades on 6 Unix servers\r\n•	Split Unix cluster that contains GBSWIDB8 & GBSWIDB9\r\no	Then split same cluster servers GBSWIDB3, GBSWIDB4, GBSWIDB5 & GBSWIDB6\r\n•	Firmware upgrade on Superdomes.\r\n•	Monthly Windows patching\r\n•	6 monthly Unix patching – next scheduled for September 2014\r\n•	DR13 rehearsal – 6th – 24th October. Although not an outage will include due to resource requirements to cover.\r\n•	Oracle database upgrades, this includes Unix OS upgrades and SAP Kernel upgrades as will be performed within same activity.\r\n\r\nPlease get back to me with any additional points by 15:00 today.\r\n\r\nMany thanks\r\n',	'2014-07-07'),
(44,	0,	'',	'CREATE DATABASE permission denied in database \'master\'.',	'Permission denied is a security so you need to add a \"User\" permission..\r\n\r\nRight click you database(which is .mdf file) and then properties\r\nGo to security tab\r\nClick Continue button\r\nClick Add button\r\nClick Advance button\r\nAnother window will show, then you click the \"Find Now\" button on the right side.\r\nOn the fields below, go to the bottom most and click the \"Users\". Click OK.\r\nClick the permission \"Users\" that you have been created, then Check the full control checkbox.',	'2014-07-23'),
