(48,	11,	'',	'BB / Prio 2 / E2-IM003238557 / EXT000000008538',	'1.) reported the issue from BB team\r\n2.) immidiade asked for the action towards DB team\r\n3.) DB team recognized that mirroring failover has been initiated \r\n4.) couple of database including BESMgmt were in Recovery state\r\n5.) DB team has fixed the issue byt restarting of the both instances\r\n6.) BESMgmt status is back online\r\n7.) BB team informed about the status...\r\n8.) BB team has confirmed that BB is back operational',	'2014-09-09'),
(49,	11,	'',	'EXT8398 /PFS ticketno. IC14043292 \"E-Mail not working via Blackberry',	'\r\nBetween the servers dusv1323.gsa.westlb.net and dusv1324.gsa.westlb.net is implemented high availability solution that should guarantee the service operation in case of unexpected outage. Something has initiated failover and the database have switched to the second node. From unknown reason the databases stayed in not operational status and were unable to switch into operational status even after minutes…So we had to manually restart the instance to bright the databases online.\r\n\r\n1.)	DBA has connected to the server dusv1323.gsa.westlb.net and checked situation\r\n2.)	He noticed that there mirroring failover has been initiated but some databases have been in Recovery state\r\n3.)	He has restarted the instance\r\n4.)	The databases especially BESMgmt have come back online and operational\r\n5.)	DBA has restarted also dusv1324.gsa.westlb.net to initiate failover from this node to the original one.\r\n6.)	Called back to verify if BB is working again\r\n7.)	BB team has confirmed everything is working properly',	'2014-09-10'),
(50,	16,	'',	'SQL cluster reinstallation',	'1.       Move all data on one node\r\n2.       Remove the second node from the SQL cluster\r\n3.       Destroy Win cluster with having one node keeping whole service keep running. \r\n4.       Reinstall one node with Win 2008 (from 2003)+ full patching and create one node cluster here\r\n5.       Install also one node SQL 2008 R2 cluster + patching\r\n6.       Mirror  the databases between SQL 2005 and SQL2008 and transfer all data from first node to new one (depends on database size – 4 hours)\r\n7.       Break database mirror between two servers and the new server will take role of service holder (ask customer test)\r\n8.       Reinstall first node to Win 2008 and add it into the cluster\r\n9.       Install SQL 2008 R2 on first node with adding to the SQL cluster\r\n10.   Test if everything is working\r\n',	'2014-09-10'),
